  "id": "PEP 351",
  "name": "Introduction to Planetary Science",
  "description": "This course introduces basic concepts of planetary science through the development of simple physical models. The first part of the course studies the planetary formation and related problems - evolution of the planet-satellite systems, orbital stability and impact events. The second part studies planets as equilibrium systems - topics include planetary atmospheres, climate cycles, seismic activity, and magnetism. The course concludes with the topics of current interest such as global warming, extra-solar planets, and planetary habitability.",
